  "text": "Embryo cryopreservation has decreased the number of fresh embryo transfers and maximized the effectiveness of the IVF cycle. Similarly, embryo cryopreservation is a crucial tool in cases of cancelled embryo transfer (ET) due to ovarian hyperstimulation risk, endometrial bleeding and elevated serum progesterone levels on the day of triggering. Embryo cryopreservation has enhanced the clinical benefits and cumulative conception rates possible for couples following a single cycle of ovarian stimulation and IVF [CITATION_1] .",
